### Item 1. Approving the Agenda

Agenda moved by JD, Seconded by OK

The agenda carries unanimously

### Item 2. Approval of the minutes from the last meeting

Minutes were incomplete. Request to add the minutes. Will be discussed at the next meeting
Mikael moved second by Heather

Aye: JH, CH, HR, JD, IJ,  DW, CN, Beam, OK, MVJ
Nay: None
Passed unanimously

### Item 3a. Pull Request #403 & 404 by Tavaresh Isa

Before the floor: JD and MVJ asked IJ if JH is willing to would be willing to amend the proposal to fuse both conditions (403&404) into one rule. 
IJ: proposes to skip 403 and discuss only 404
404 becomes 403, and 403 is dropped before going to the floor

Motion by pull request by IJ to create a new rule 403: If a player needs more time to think about the matter before voting, he/she may request to postpone voting to the next plenary session.
Second by: no need to be second because the discussion started

Aye: JH, IJ
Nay: CH, HR, JD, DW, CN, Beam, OK, MVJ

The motion fails. 

Point updates:
IJ loses 10

### Item 3b. Pull Request #404

Motion by pull request by MVJ to create a new Rule 404: Any number stated with numerals in the body of mutable rules is to be doubled before interpreting the rule.
Any number spelled out with letters remains unchanged.
Seconded by JD

JH: Motion to amend the rule proposal to change the phrasing of to be doubled to be multiplied by the number two
Seconded by MVJ

Olga: Motion to amend an amendment: change the number two to number five because five is much easier to multiply by
Seconded by JH

Votes for amendment to the amendment (multiply by 5):
Aye: JH,  JD,  OK 
Nay:  CH, HR, IJ,  DW, CN, Beam, MVJ
Amendment to amendment failed

Votes for the amendment (multiply by 2):
Aye: JH, CH, JD, IJ
Nay: HR, DW, CN, Beam, OK, MVJ
Amedmant failed

Votes for the rule:
Aye: JH,  JD, DW, MVJ
Nay: CH, HR, IJ, CN, Beam, OK,
Rule 404 failed

MVJ loses 10

### Item 3c. Pull Request #405

Motion by pull request by HB to create a new Rule 405: If a vote passes with an amendment, the player who introduced the amendment retains half the points, rounded up to the nearest integer, of the player who introduced the new rule.
Seconded by OK

JH: motion to amend: If a rule change passes with an amendment, each player who introduced an adopted amendment to the rule change will be awarded points equal to half of the points awarded to the player who proposed the rule change, rounded up to the nearest integer.
Seconded by DW

Votes for the amendment:
Aye: JH, CH, HR, JD, DW, CN, Beam, MVJ
Nay: IJ, OK,
Amendment to the rule passed

Votes for the rule:
Aye: JH,  HR,  IJ,  DW, CN, Beam, 
Nay: CH, JD, OK, MVJ
Rule passes

Heather got 95 points
JH got 23

### Item 4. New Business

No new business introduced.

MVJ adjourns the meeting at 3:53pm
